✅ Parameters in Azure Pipelines (one-line style)
name:
displayName:
type:
default:
values:

string parameter → Accepts single-line text input at runtime.                type: string
boolean parameter → Allows true/false selection in pipeline run.             type: boolean
choice parameter → Provides dropdown selection with predefined values.      
number parameter → Accepts numeric input.                                    type: numberlist
object parameter → Used to pass complex structured data (arrays/maps).       type: object    --used for tags

>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>>

Simple pipeline with variable and parameters

trigger:
- main

pool:
  vmImage: ubuntu-latest

parameters:
- name: appName
  type: string
  default: myapp

- name: env
  type: string
  default: dev
  values:
  - dev
  - test
  - prod

variables:
  myVar: hello

steps:
- script: echo $(myVar)
  displayName: Print Variable

- script: echo ${{ parameters.appName }}
  displayName: Print String Parameter

- script: echo ${{ parameters.env }}
  displayName: Print Choice Parameter

