✅ 1. What is a Task
👉 Task = predefined action performed in a pipeline

Used inside steps
Executes a specific operation
Provided by Azure DevOps or extensions


✅ 2. One-line definition
👉 “Task is a reusable unit of work that performs a specific operation like build, test, deploy, or script execution.”

✅ 3. Basic Syntax
YAMLsteps:- task: TaskName@Version  inputs:    key: valueShow more lines

✅ 4. Simple Example
YAMLsteps:- task: Bash@3  inputs:    targetType: 'inline'    script: echo "Hello World"Show more lines

✅ 5. Types of Task Options (important)

✅ 1. Script Tasks
👉 Run commands/scripts

Bash@3 → Linux shell
CmdLine@2 → Windows CMD
PowerShell@2 → PowerShell

✅ Example:
YAML- script: echo "Hello"Show more lines

✅ 2. Build Tasks
👉 Build applications

Maven@4 → Java build
Gradle@2 → Gradle projects
VSBuild@1 → .NET build

✅ Example:
YAML- task: Maven@4Show more lines

✅ 3. Test Tasks
👉 Run test cases

VSTest@2 → .NET tests
JUnit → Java tests


✅ 4. Docker Tasks
👉 Build and push containers

Docker@2

✅ Example:
YAML- task: Docker@2  inputs:    command: buildAndPushShow more lines

✅ 5. Deployment Tasks
👉 Deploy applications

AzureWebApp@1 → App Service
Kubernetes@1 → K8s deploy
AzureContainerApps@1 → Container Apps


✅ 6. Utility Tasks
👉 General operations

CopyFiles@2 → copy files
PublishBuildArtifacts@1 → publish artifacts
